        <div class="media-body">
            <h3 class="media-heading">Watering Tips</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Water a lawn only when it needs it. Overwatering can lead to higher water bills, weed growth, extra mowing, and fertilizer runoff.</li>
                <li>Instead of watering every day, only water a couple of times a week depending on the need.</li>
                <li>The water should go about 6-8 inches deep into the soil.</li>
                <li>Watering in the morning is best to reduce the amount of evaporation that can lead to water waste.</li>
                <li>Make sure sprinklers are not wasting water by watering the driveway or sidewalk.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
